Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick rounds. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

In a small #pot, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3⁄4 cup water (1 1⁄2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, toss carrots on one side of a #baking sheet with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}. (For 4 servings, spread out across entire sheet.)

Roast carrots on top rack for ~{10%minutes} (you'll add the pork then).

> For 4 servings, roast carrots on top rack for 10 minutes, add the chicken then.

> For beef version, roast carrots on top rack for 13 minutes, then add the beef.

Meanwhile, pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a large #pan over medium heat. Add beef and sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{2-4%minutes} per side.

Once carrots have roasted 10 minutes, stir carrots and carefully place seared beef on opposite side. (For 4 servings, place beef on a second #baking sheet; roast on middle rack.)

Return to top rack; roast until beef is cooked to desired doneness, ~{5-10%minutes} more.

> Swap in chicken for pork. Sear 2-3 minutes per side. Once carrots have roasted 10 minutes, stir carrots and place chicken on opposite side of sheet. Roast until cooked through, 10-12 minutes more.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

When beef and carrots have 5 minutes left, melt @butter{1%tbsp} in pan used for beef over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @bulgogi sauce{4%ounce} and 1 TBSP water. Bring to a simmer, stirring, until warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat.

> If sauce is too thick, stir in a splash more water.

Fluff rice with a #fork. Stir in half the lemon zest (add more if you like), @butter{1%tbsp}, and a squeeze of lemon juice; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Thinly slice beef crosswise.

> Thinly slice chicken or beef against the grain.

Divide rice, beef, and carrots between plates. Drizzle beef with sauce. Sprinkle with scallion greens and @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.